  "fun_fact": "India is rapidly getting hotter, but not all at once. A hidden reality that most people don't see: women carry a disproportionate and highly gendered burden of heat stress. Hormonal fluctuations, body composition, and metabolic rates all affect thermoregulation, making women more susceptible to dehydration, fatigue, and heat-related illness. And pregnant women face even greater risks due. <a href=\"https://www.downtoearth.org.in/climate-change/indias-future-climate-resilience-will-depend-on-its-ability-to-build-a-public-healthcare-system-that-recognises-heat-as-a-highly-gendered-disaster\" target=\"_blank\">Read more</a>",
